          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgzar7BOYo5G0GMT6G4mG-Hz2980vrm2vGSH5fR3Qh5oMaEiQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I just want to share my recent experience with Dr. Javadi Noosheen at NY Medical. I am not a person to get myself checked out, the most recent months I have been feeling unwell and looking for answers. I appreciate her listening and willingness to find solutions. She is extremely professional and explains things in ways I am able to understand. I cannot stress how important it is for your primary care doctor to do so! Also, side note, the front desk staff and nurses are just as amazing, very polite and helpful. Thank you!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2w5b1MzVTBSMFJ3VmxaYU9HeFFXa3hWV0VsMmJHYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xb2cd13949eaff9e3!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOl9oS3U0R0RwVlZaOGxQWkxVWEl2bGc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "5 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-01-15T19:45:37+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Sam Hodgdon",
          "rating": 2,
          "contributor_id": "117624997953449951309",
          "user_review_count": 6,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi-4ShpXCf-bJtN2LA3Mc6TOyever5MzM-ChC0ds-ph4ffPfttZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "The scheduling availability was very helpful, and most of the staff was kind enough, although a few experiences left a bad taste. During one appointment where I was very sick and just wanted to get back home to lay down, the doctor took a phone call. She said her kid was sick and she needed to take it which I completely understand, but I could hear the person on the other line say it was not an emergency. She proceeded to stay on the phone for almost 5 minutes, while in the room with me, on a non emergent call? She was also clearly sick, and barely wearing a mask which\u2026 yikes.\nDuring my last visit for a medication refill, I felt shamed for not coming in, she said I was \u201cvery overdue\u201d for my annual and had a pretty judgemental tone (at that time I was maybe a month late for my annual visit, if that, and had already told her I was planning on booking it in the next couple weeks once my schedule allowed). That\u2019s not the way to encourage patients to seek care, and it made me feel pretty embarrassed. This was the nail in the coffin, and I have found a different provider.\nI also find it interesting that all of the reviews mentioning disappointment/frustration with their weight loss drug advertising seem to have been deleted. I feel the need to add this to my review, since it\u2019s something that deterred me from seeking care at this office and is something people should know if they\u2019re considering coming here. I have never expressed interest in this, and my doctor has never recommended it. Yet, during the first year and a half I was a patient here, I received three times the amount of emails advertising these medications than I did about the practice or my own care. When I expressed that this was difficult for me and was bringing up past issues that had been resolved and requested to be removed from that list, they claimed there was no way to unsubscribe from those without also missing important practice updates. I will say, the phone representative I spoke to was very kind and apologetic, but that sentiment was not shared by the practice at large. Feels a bit ridiculous to not have a separate email list so that they could be compassionate towards their patients differing needs. I know they can genuinely be helpful for some patients, however I think it\u2019s unethical to send out frequent blanket advertisements for a medication without consideration to who that\u2019s going to.\n\nAll in all, I would not recommend this practice unless you just need a quick checkup and don\u2019t mind being hounded about the latest weight loss deal.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xWR04xOXhWV0Z4VUdKSVJ6RnVVVzFxVGxCNlZVRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xb2cd13949eaff9e3!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlVGN19xVWFxUGJIRzFuUW1qTlB6VUE%7C%7C?hl=en",
